Package ca.cgjennings.ui.textedit.completion

This package provides the support classes needed to implement code completion.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    CNode<T extends CNode>
    This interface describes a node in a tree of completion alternatives.
    CodeCompleter
    A code completer offers alternatives that can be inserted at a given offset to complete an incomplete segment of code.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbbreviationTable
    An abbreviation table stores a set of abbreviations.
    AbbreviationTable.Expansion
    Encapsulates an expansion result from AbbreviationTable.expandAbbreviation(java.lang.String).
    APIDatabase
    A shared database of cached Java class and package information.
    APILeaf
    This is the superclass of all API nodes that cannot have children, such as named constants.
    APINode
    An abstract completion node base class that represents part of a static API, such as a class or package.
    ClassNode
    A node representing a Java package in a PackageRoot.
    CodeAlternative
    A code alternative represents one possible option for completing a code fragment.
    CompletionPopup
    A popup control that displays code completion options.
    DefaultCNode<T extends CNode>
    A default, mutable implementation of the CNode interface.
    DefaultCodeAlternative
    A default implementation of CodeAlternative.
    PackageNode
    A node representing a Java package in a PackageRoot.
    PackageRoot
    The mutable root of a tree of package and class information.
    PlainTextCompleter
    A code completer for plain text that offers to complete partially typed words using a spelling checker dictionary.
    ScriptCodeCompleter
    A code completer for JavaScript source files.
    ScriptCompleter  
    ScriptCompletionContext
    Describes the context in which a scripting code completion occurs.

Package ca.cgjennings.ui.textedit.completion Description

This package provides the support classes needed to implement code completion.
